text: London Has Fallen... Interesting title, considering the film's content. Perhaps it's a calculated risk-aversion move by the filmmakers, considering how the rest of the world isn't particularly bothered by the notion of the American president under attack (indeed, why would they be? Who'd be fussed about, say, a threat to the government of Switzerland? Or terrorists trying to destroy the Second House of Lichenstein?) These kind of US-centric films playing on Americans' over-zealous patriotism just don't have the same reach/appeal internationally - so I wonder if that slightly evasive film title will help sell the film to international audiences? Let's see...

Between these two dates, they were able to edit a lot of visual effects, and many of the unappealing aspects of this trailer were fixed. Don't you just wonder why the gross was more than three times the budget? Well, hell, that's because the movie was appealing to the common people.
